cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper is about improving the sample efficiency of deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of reinforcement learning algorithms such as DDPG and the proposed DVG and DVPG algorithms suggest that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on continuous control tasks and the use of analytical gradients suggest that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of value gradients and policy gradients suggest that it could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
